text.tspan: There are a number of challenges facing individuals and organizations when it
comes to diversity, equity, and inclusion, and there is an explicit need for
clarifying what diversity, equity, and inclusion are and why they matter. Thus, it
is important to define and describe the concepts of diversity, equity, and
inclusion separately to grasp the concept as a whole.
The combination of these three factors are essential for a workplace
environment that fosters positivity and authenticity, both of which are essential
for creating stronger, better, and more welcoming organizations.
What is Diversity,
Equity, & Inclusion?
Diversity
The extent to which a group of people includes
members that differ in socially meaningful ways from
each other at work.
Equity
The existence of fair and just practices within
organizations so that all members can thrive. It is a
feeling that people are being treated fairly.
Inclusion
The process of ensuring that people from different
backgrounds are invited to and appreciated in the
workplace.
